      "content": "thanks for the lead. the thing is, it's not just about \"mentions\" in archives. i have the 1954 Treaty of Karstov here—it's a physical document signed by the regional administrators and the protectorate's council. it's basically the legal proof that the Aethelgard bloodline holds sovereign rights that were never officially renounced, just suppressed. based on what you know about international law, if i can prove this treaty was validly signed before the annexation, does that give me a legal basis to claim the title of Sovereign? like, can a state's legitimacy be argued if its existence was forcibly erased from the map?",
